    "Generally, cardiovascular activity was not the unique parameter measured in the experiences.",
    "Electrodermal activity, shown in dark blue, was also a widely measured physiological parameter (17.5%).",
    "It provides information on the user's level of physical arousal and tension.",
    "More than in any others, the electrodermal activity was the parameter used in the following three fields (20%): Psychology, Ergonomics, and Military.",
    "These categories coincide with those in which cardiovascular activity was measured most of all."
